 of 1919, and ultimately set the literary agenda for later, more celebrated texts about the war.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticismy20th century. 0aAmerican literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xLiterature and the warxElectronic booksxCriticism, interpretation, etc.zUnited States. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xLiterature and the warxUnited StatesxUnited StatesxElectronic booksxCriticism, interpretation, etc. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918zUnited StatesxLiterature and the war. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311053800708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213249423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300213249.jpg  a978-3-11-053800-7  YUP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles